    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, p. 36 n. <citedRange>7</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2183</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>086800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.58</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἄριστις"><unclear>Ἄ</unclear>ριστ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ις</supplied></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Πατρι_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Πατρι</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Arist<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">is</supplied> fils de Patri<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Arist<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">is</supplied> son of Patri<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Arist<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">is</supplied> figlio di Patri<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>From the bad photograph available, it is difficult to know how many letters are missing at right. If at l. 1 only two letters are missing, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἄριστις</foreign> 
                    is a very good restoration. In that case, only two letters would be missing also at l. 2, where <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πάτρις</foreign>, although unattested, would be a dialectally 
                    regular short form of compounds like <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πατρόφιλος</foreign>.</p>
	           <p>On the other hand, if there is enough space to admit <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πάτριππος</foreign> as the father's name, as suggested by Reynolds, then <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἄριστις</foreign> 
	               would be rather short for the son's name and one would suggest some longer name, such as <foreign xml:lang="frc">Ἀριστέας</foreign> or even <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀρίστιππος</foreign>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
